HEADWORD: Ullmannite
<hw>Ull"mann*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named after
<person>J. C. <etsep>Ullman</etsep></person>, a German chemist.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A brittle mineral of a steel-gray color and
metallic luster, containing antimony, arsenic, sulphur, and
nickel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ulluco</ent>⟦br⟧
